1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,270
[I Don't Want To Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:42,740 --> 00:01:43,320
Mom.

4
00:01:44,539 --> 00:01:46,520
Can I call your full name in future?

5
00:01:46,520 --> 00:01:47,229
Why?

6
00:01:48,140 --> 00:01:49,620
Our teacher told us that

7
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:53,490
the best way to get along with parents
is to be friends.

8
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:57,850
Don't friends call each other by names?

9
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,060
Can't we be friends?

10
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:00,900
We can.

11
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,670
You can call me whatever you want.

12
00:02:02,670 --> 00:02:04,070
Hurry up and eat. It's getting cold.

13
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,380
Li Qing Tong.

14
00:02:06,380 --> 00:02:07,220
What?

15
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,960
Our teacher is getting married.

16
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:11,900
She invited all our classmates
to her wedding.

17
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,540
Do you want to go with us?

18
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:14,800
Yes.

19
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,310
How can I let you go alone?

20
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:21,260
Li Qing Tong.

21
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:22,230
What?

22
00:02:22,860 --> 00:02:24,250
Our teacher doesn't have a husband.

23
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,760
She's always in a hurry to get married.

24
00:02:26,300 --> 00:02:27,900
You don't have a husband anymore.

25
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:29,660
When are you getting married?

26
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:32,380
If I were not married,
where did you come from?

27
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:33,860
Listen.

28
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:35,000
I was married.

29
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,850
So I don't need to
get married again, okay?

30
00:02:38,900 --> 00:02:39,829
Li Qing Tong

31
00:02:39,829 --> 00:02:40,670
Call me mom.

32
00:02:41,340 --> 00:02:42,470
Shut up and eat.

33
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:47,430
[Episode 24:
I Don't Want To Be Friends With You]

34
00:02:47,430 --> 00:02:48,440
Be careful. The soup is hot.

35
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,200
[Li Qing Tong.]

36
00:02:56,030 --> 00:02:58,390
[I'm sorry that this is how]

37
00:02:59,070 --> 00:02:59,950
[our first letter is like.]

38
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:02,080
[Li Qing Tong]

39
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,600
[For a long time,
I was actually confident]

40
00:03:04,270 --> 00:03:06,250
[about our relationship.]

41
00:03:07,210 --> 00:03:09,310
[We have supported each other.]

42
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,500
[I helped you become a new Li Qing Tong]

43
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:14,430
[and you protected me.]

44
00:03:14,430 --> 00:03:16,370
[I get to become the Wu Zhi Xun
I used to be.]

45
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,470
[From now on,]

46
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:21,780
[I shall continue to be the selfish
and indifferent jerk I was.]

47
00:03:22,290 --> 00:03:23,510
[I'll try to climb heights]

48
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:25,820
[and make myself unable to stop.]

49
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:27,370
[Only then]

50
00:03:27,610 --> 00:03:29,340
[can I always remind myself]

51
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:32,620
[of the wonderful person
I have lost for this.]

52
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,360
[And you]

53
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:38,079
[have to continue to be yourself.]

54
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,520
[You have as many advantages
as you have your disadvantages.]

55
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,140
Okay, look at the camera.

56
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:42,780
[But you don't care about
other people's opinions.]

57
00:03:43,329 --> 00:03:44,930
[This is how you should be.]

58
00:03:45,510 --> 00:03:46,730
[Never change it.]

59
00:03:47,700 --> 00:03:48,450
[Li Qing Tong.]

60
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,600
[I have learned a lot of equations,]

61
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,110
[formulas and theorems]

62
00:03:52,860 --> 00:03:54,790
[but I can't find one]

63
00:03:54,790 --> 00:03:56,430
[to prove that I loved you.]

64
00:03:57,690 --> 00:03:58,740
Wait.

65
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,170
[So,]

66
00:04:00,170 --> 00:04:01,430
[I won't prove it anymore.]

67
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,290
[I'll remember our past.]

68
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,260
[But I hope you can forget it]

69
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,900
[and then forget me.]

70
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,000
[I'm sorry.]

71
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:41,500
I'm ready.

72
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:42,760
Okay.

73
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,020
Three,

74
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:45,150
two,

75
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:46,409
one.

76
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:49,650
[Registry of Marriage,
Tieyuan Civil Affairs Bureau]

77
00:04:49,650 --> 00:04:50,700
That's enough.

78
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:51,909
Don't cry anymore.

79
00:04:51,909 --> 00:04:54,350
Or else people will think that
I have bought you as my wife.

80
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:58,760
Give me one yuan.

81
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:01,110
I'll pretend you bought me.

82
00:05:04,770 --> 00:05:05,650
Ten yuan.

83
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:07,830
After all, you are valuable to me.

84
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,860
How did we get married?

85
00:05:22,110 --> 00:05:24,840
It's too sudden.
My mom doesn't even know it.

86
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:26,900
My uncle doesn't know either.

87
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:30,840
What should we do from now on?

88
00:05:31,230 --> 00:05:32,780
Do what we should do.

89
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,210
It's all fake anyway.

90
00:05:34,210 --> 00:05:35,430
It's just a formality.

91
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:44,960
Li Qing Tong.

92
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:47,980
No wedding

93
00:05:47,980 --> 00:05:49,280
and no wedding dress.

94
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:50,320
I owe you all that.

95
00:05:51,090 --> 00:05:51,850
I promise you

96
00:05:51,850 --> 00:05:53,230
I'll never take advantage of you.

97
00:05:54,030 --> 00:05:55,250
When the child is born,

98
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,210
we'll get a divorce.

99
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,730
I'll never pester you.

100
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:06,160
But before the baby is born,

101
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,590
you're my wife.

102
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:09,740
You've to listen to me
about you and the child.

103
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:16,500
Did you really owe me
in the previous life?

104
00:06:17,170 --> 00:06:18,560
I haven't lived to understand this life.

105
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,810
Don't mention the previous life.

106
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:21,570
Let's go, my dear.

107
00:06:21,570 --> 00:06:23,090
Do you want to follow me back
to the bathhouse for dinner?

108
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:27,000
Shouldn't you eat something good
for the first day of marriage?

109
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,800
No.

110
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:31,160
I will make you braised meat
with vermicelli

111
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:31,790
and also...

112
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:37,880
You two should go
after eating the dumplings.

113
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:39,640
Don't worry about me.

114
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:43,970
You can come back anytime
when you miss home.

115
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:47,580
If you run out of money,

116
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,180
just call me.

117
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:51,909
You two can be

118
00:06:51,909 --> 00:06:53,080
each other's companion

119
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,850
and take care of each other.

120
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,200
I'm relieved.

121
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:09,870
Aunt.

122
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,530
The dumplings you make
are the best dumplings ever.

123
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,920
Can you show me how to make the stuffings?

124
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:20,380
Tong Tong loves celery stuffings.

125
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:25,080
You have to chop the celery
into small pieces.

126
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:27,770
When buying meat

127
00:07:28,610 --> 00:07:30,250
at the market,

128
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:32,100
let the seller mince it for you.

129
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:35,540
It's very tiring to do it yourself.

130
00:07:59,780 --> 00:08:00,320
Tong,

131
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,380
pour me a drink too.

132
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,190
Li,

133
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:40,179
time for dinner.

134
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,020
Let's get started.

135
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:46,990
Is it a girl?

136
00:09:49,810 --> 00:09:51,060
I have no idea.

137
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,720
The doctor didn't let me ask.

138
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:02,120
Are you really not
going to tell Wu Zhi Xun?

139
00:10:09,970 --> 00:10:11,860
He has his own life to live.

140
00:10:12,740 --> 00:10:14,470
This is my child.

141
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:16,860
I think it's all good.

142
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,430
You probably won't

143
00:10:21,940 --> 00:10:23,450
persuade me to...

144
00:10:23,450 --> 00:10:24,800
Give birth to her.

145
00:10:26,380 --> 00:10:27,910
No matter how hard it will be.

146
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:37,020
Li Qing Tong.

147
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,880
Having a baby will be very difficult.

148
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:44,160
But no matter how difficult it is,

149
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,220
always remember to

150
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:49,540
spend every holiday with her.

151
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:52,100
You should take her to eat delicious food

152
00:10:52,980 --> 00:10:54,200
and buy her fun toys.

153
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,090
You must keep your word

154
00:10:56,090 --> 00:10:57,350
and can't always lie to her.

155
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,870
You should buy her presents

156
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:02,180
on her birthday.

157
00:11:04,490 --> 00:11:05,910
The most important thing is that

158
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:09,990
you two find a proper house.

159
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:11,840
Don't keep moving all the time.

160
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:16,250
Don't let her live a displaced life.

161
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,050
What's wrong with you?

162
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:22,340
Why are you saying this to me?

163
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,760
Anyway,

164
00:11:25,070 --> 00:11:26,830
it's hard to be a child too.

165
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:30,950
I'm a terrible child.

166
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:33,550
I always felt that my mom

167
00:11:33,550 --> 00:11:34,600
didn't love

168
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:36,450
or care about me.

169
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,630
I talk back to her every day.

170
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:42,240
Thinking about it now,

171
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,700
I feel sorry for her.

172
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:51,190
So,

173
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:54,680
you must never let your child
be like me in future.

174
00:11:55,890 --> 00:11:58,120
I'm the worst daughter in the world.

175
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,770
Don't worry.

176
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:04,880
Your mother definitely won't
think of you like that.

177
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,650
She won't dislike you

178
00:12:06,650 --> 00:12:08,540
or think you are terrible.

179
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:13,620
I can understand what my dad said now.

180
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:16,630
The child hasn't been born yet,

181
00:12:17,650 --> 00:12:20,170
but I've already started to worry.

182
00:12:20,630 --> 00:12:22,130
I worry every day about

183
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,240
the things I do and whether

184
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,960
I've done them well.

185
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:27,850
I worry every day about

186
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:31,130
my ability to raise her all by myself.

187
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,710
I also worry about

188
00:12:35,710 --> 00:12:37,850
my ability to give her a good life.

189
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,710
Li Qing Tong.

190
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,650
Both of you will be absolutely fine.

191
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:46,670
Really.

192
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,560
You definitely will.

193
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:31,060
Take care of yourself.

194
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,020
You take care too.

195
00:13:42,070 --> 00:13:43,200
Goodbye aunt.

196
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,010
Go back inside.

197
00:14:00,590 --> 00:14:02,100
[Some things have ended]

198
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,490
[and some things have started.]

199
00:14:03,910 --> 00:14:05,630
[We just grew up overnight.]

200
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,990
[After losing those important people,]

201
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,680
[those who are by our sides
will become extremely precious.]

202
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:21,550
Li Qing Tong.

203
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:23,100
We'll have dumplings today.

204
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:25,660
Li Qing Tong.

205
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:31,580
[So I started to cherish the time
I had with Li Qing Tong.]

206
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,230
[Even though I don't know
when I will leave,]

207
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:36,880
[I will still spend every final minute
with all my heart.]

208
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:40,820
How do you feel?

209
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:42,590
It's getting increasingly
frequent these days.

210
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:44,220
[Because in this world,]

211
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,860
[I'm her best friend.]

212
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,560
You are not going to the south with me?

213
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:52,620
No.

214
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,320
Take care.

215
00:15:03,590 --> 00:15:04,340
Bye-bye.

216
00:15:10,470 --> 00:15:12,700
[Chen Jun He also gave up the opportunity
to start a business]

217
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,850
[and stayed back to become
a nominal father-to-be.]

218
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,620
[He seemed to have never
taken care of anyone before,]

219
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,810
[so everything was
very difficult for him.]

220
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:28,910
I'm sleepy.

221
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:30,550
Sleepy?

222
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,720
[But when I was with them,]

223
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:38,490
[it felt like we are a
wonderful family of three.]

224
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:40,800
[It felt like mom and dad were skylarking]

225
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,480
[while waiting for my birth.]

226
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:44,370
[Although to be honest,]

227
00:15:44,370 --> 00:15:46,680
[I'm not sure if this kid is me.]

228
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:48,650
[That's not important.]

229
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:51,760
[I really want to
live like this every day.]

230
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,780
[I want to see the birth of this child.]

231
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,830
[What will she look like?]

232
00:15:56,460 --> 00:15:57,130
[Will she]

233
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,560
[be me?]

234
00:16:04,780 --> 00:16:06,150
How was your check-up
at the hospital today?

235
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,170
Everything is fine?

236
00:16:07,580 --> 00:16:08,460
Yes.

237
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:09,360
Everything is fine.

238
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,410
That's good.

239
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:11,620
Just be careful with what you do.

240
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:16,830
Duan Xiao called

241
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,270
and said he is back.

242
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,610
He will drop by for a visit tomorrow.

243
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:26,910
He is...

244
00:16:26,910 --> 00:16:28,510
We haven't seen each other
for a long time.

245
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:29,180
He wanted to have a gathering

246
00:16:29,180 --> 00:16:30,440
and visit Li Qing Tong too.

247
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,550
Are you okay?

248
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,430
The onion is making me tear up.

249
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:32,720
Time for dinner.

250
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:35,500
I bought a roast chicken today.

251
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:36,490
We have an extra dish today.

252
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:39,610
I fear that you don't
have enough nutrition.

253
00:17:39,610 --> 00:17:40,160
Here.

254
00:17:40,370 --> 00:17:40,960
Take this.

255
00:17:48,890 --> 00:17:49,610
Swift Leg,

256
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,530
this is for you.

257
00:17:51,290 --> 00:17:52,090
Thank you.

258
00:17:58,260 --> 00:17:58,970
Don't you think

259
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:01,120
it'd be nice if we can wash all these down

260
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:01,960
with the soda of Tieyuan?

261
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:02,710
No.

262
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,520
You can't drink carbonated
drinks at this time.

263
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,390
Why don't we eat out tomorrow?

264
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,230
Right.

265
00:18:10,480 --> 00:18:12,030
Let's go out and eat
something nice tomorrow.

266
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:12,960
It's on him.

267
00:18:14,670 --> 00:18:15,980
I need to work overtime tomorrow.

268
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:17,410
You two just go.

269
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,530
What are you doing here?

270
00:18:42,530 --> 00:18:43,530
Go back and lie down.

271
00:18:45,130 --> 00:18:46,350
I come to accompany you.

272
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:48,230
For what?

273
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:51,050
Nothing.

274
00:18:51,390 --> 00:18:52,690
I just want to accompany you.

275
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:17,380
It's been a long time.

276
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:20,240
Why are you here alone?

277
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,900
Come in.

278
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:30,570
Where's Chen Jun He?

279
00:19:31,830 --> 00:19:33,560
He said he still has something
to do in the kindergarten.

280
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,050
Take a seat.

281
00:19:51,150 --> 00:19:52,660
How is life recently?

282
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:53,800
Are you getting used to it?

283
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:55,890
I'm used to it a long ago time.

284
00:20:12,780 --> 00:20:15,550
Hua was called back to work today.

285
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:16,800
Why don't you wait for a while?

286
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,030
She might be back soon.

287
00:20:23,950 --> 00:20:28,660
[Arts and Crafts Section]

288
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:31,350
What are you looking at, Mr Chen?

289
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:33,030
I'm looking at the clouds.

290
00:20:33,030 --> 00:20:35,080
What's so special about the clouds?

291
00:20:35,830 --> 00:20:36,300
Come here.

292
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:37,440
Look.

293
00:20:37,930 --> 00:20:40,080
People are like clouds,

294
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,470
gathered and scattered.

295
00:20:41,850 --> 00:20:43,190
When the wind blows,

296
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:44,830
there is nothing left.

297
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:48,100
I'm sorry, Mr Chen.

298
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,780
You had to watch over my child again.

299
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:50,500
It's fine.

300
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,420
We're colleagues.

301
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:52,980
I learned about childcare before.

302
00:20:53,550 --> 00:20:54,820
Say goodbye to Mr Chen.

303
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:55,530
Goodbye.

304
00:20:55,530 --> 00:20:56,170
Bye.

305
00:20:56,170 --> 00:20:56,840
Let's go.

306
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,230
I'm leaving.

307
00:21:16,910 --> 00:21:17,460
No, wait...

308
00:21:17,460 --> 00:21:18,850
How about waiting a little longer?

309
00:21:18,850 --> 00:21:20,780
She might really be back very soon.

310
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:21,320
It's fine.

311
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,460
I'm here to see you.

312
00:21:26,490 --> 00:21:27,500
I'll see you off.

313
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,040
If you need any help,

314
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:43,960
just tell me.

315
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,020
Have a safe trip back.

316
00:21:47,780 --> 00:21:48,450
Bye.

317
00:22:04,050 --> 00:22:07,180
[Inpatient Department]

318
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:19,910
Did the doctor say when
I'll go into labour?

319
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,270
It should be these few days.

320
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:23,520
By the way,

321
00:22:23,520 --> 00:22:25,370
Ba Dan and Fan Shui Shui
are on their way here.

322
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,180
Don't let them come.

323
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:28,100
It's too troublesome

324
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:28,650
to come here.

325
00:22:28,650 --> 00:22:30,080
I've told them that too.

326
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:31,880
Fan Shui Shui said she would come anyway.

327
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,020
I couldn't stop her.

328
00:22:34,230 --> 00:22:35,960
Fan Shui Shui is still
as anxious as she always is.

329
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:41,330
I'm hungry.

330
00:22:41,790 --> 00:22:42,970
I want to eat canned food.

331
00:22:43,390 --> 00:22:45,490
Haven't you just eaten?

332
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:46,790
Why are you hungry again?

333
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:48,770
How can I give birth without eating?

334
00:23:59,110 --> 00:23:59,740
[Li Jin Bu.]

335
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:00,670
[Li Qing Tong is about to give birth.]

336
00:24:00,670 --> 00:24:01,550
[Come back quickly.]

337
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,500
Chen Jun He.

338
00:24:06,670 --> 00:24:07,930
This time,

339
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:10,370
you must take good care of Li Qing Tong.

340
00:24:10,710 --> 00:24:11,710
[What do you mean?]

341
00:24:11,710 --> 00:24:12,640
[Come back quickly.]

342
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:56,860
Li Jin Bu.

343
00:24:58,960 --> 00:24:59,970
Li Jin Bu.

344
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:37,060
You know,

345
00:25:38,020 --> 00:25:39,790
even if I could never see you again,

346
00:25:41,090 --> 00:25:42,520
I'll still wait for you.

347
00:27:08,450 --> 00:27:09,290
Wake up.

348
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:10,800
Miss.

349
00:27:11,850 --> 00:27:12,650
Miss.

350
00:27:13,190 --> 00:27:13,950
Wake up.

351
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:16,550
Miss.

352
00:27:16,550 --> 00:27:17,220
Wake up.

353
00:27:18,190 --> 00:27:18,820
Miss.

354
00:27:23,690 --> 00:27:25,290
Finally you're awake.

355
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:27,050
Are you okay?

356
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:30,580
You fainted at the entrance
of the sauna just now.

357
00:27:36,750 --> 00:27:38,050
Where am I?

358
00:27:38,310 --> 00:27:38,940
This place?

359
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:41,960
This is Sunshine Club.

360
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:43,600
You made your way here.
Don't you know this place?

361
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,370
Where's the guy just now?

362
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:47,800
The guy?

363
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:49,390
There's no guy.

364
00:27:49,390 --> 00:27:50,230
What guy?

365
00:27:52,870 --> 00:27:54,350
What time is it now?

366
00:27:56,370 --> 00:27:57,370
It's six o'clock in the morning.

367
00:27:58,590 --> 00:27:59,980
Isn't here Tieyuan?

368
00:28:01,950 --> 00:28:02,410
Here?

369
00:28:02,880 --> 00:28:03,670
We're in Jinhai,

370
00:28:03,670 --> 00:28:04,600
not Tieyuan.

371
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:07,540
Jinhai...

372
00:28:11,990 --> 00:28:12,790
Miss,

373
00:28:13,330 --> 00:28:14,260
are you okay?

374
00:28:15,430 --> 00:28:16,780
Are you not well?

375
00:28:17,030 --> 00:28:17,620
I...

376
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:18,670
I'll call you a doctor.

377
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:24,590
Fan Shui Shui.

378
00:28:26,730 --> 00:28:27,820
I have searched everywhere.

379
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:29,460
I can't find her.

380
00:28:31,770 --> 00:28:34,080
Where do you think she is?

381
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:40,510
I'm now at the place we quarrelled.

382
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,670
I know I shouldn't have said that.

383
00:28:44,670 --> 00:28:47,060
I know I was wrong.

384
00:28:48,530 --> 00:28:50,250
Was that all really just a dream?

385
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:54,070
It was so real.

386
00:28:54,660 --> 00:28:56,890
She didn't come back all night.

387
00:28:56,890 --> 00:28:59,360
Will she be okay?

388
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:03,060
Do you think she'll be fine?

389
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,080
Mom.

390
00:29:09,860 --> 00:29:11,750
Li Jin Bu.

391
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:26,030
Why didn't you tell me...

392
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:27,250
Mom.

393
00:29:34,520 --> 00:29:36,160
I missed you.

394
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,750
Jin Bu,

395
00:30:08,750 --> 00:30:11,390
I'll make breakfast for you.

396
00:30:18,830 --> 00:30:20,000
It's still so early.

397
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:21,180
Where is she?

398
00:30:26,890 --> 00:30:27,480
Godmother.

399
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:28,230
Over here.

400
00:30:32,100 --> 00:30:33,730
What's the matter?

401
00:30:33,730 --> 00:30:34,700
Why do we have to

402
00:30:34,700 --> 00:30:35,790
come here to talk?

403
00:30:36,380 --> 00:30:38,230
I haven't seen you for a long time.

404
00:30:38,230 --> 00:30:39,150
I missed you.

405
00:30:39,150 --> 00:30:40,160
What do you mean?

406
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:42,140
We met only two days ago.

407
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,490
What would you like to drink?

408
00:30:44,490 --> 00:30:45,030
Just order.

409
00:30:45,030 --> 00:30:45,620
It's on me.

410
00:30:45,620 --> 00:30:46,280
No.

411
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:47,220
I don't want to.
I've got things to do later.

412
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,560
Tell me quickly. What's the matter?

413
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:49,740
Well,

414
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:52,000
I want to ask

415
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,270
about Chen Jun He.

416
00:30:55,450 --> 00:30:56,620
I have told you this is

417
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:57,970
matters of the adults.

418
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:00,490
I just wanted to ask

419
00:31:00,870 --> 00:31:02,510
why they got divorced.

420
00:31:03,470 --> 00:31:04,650
Your mom and Chen Jun He were just

421
00:31:04,650 --> 00:31:06,120
too short-tempered towards each other.

422
00:31:06,450 --> 00:31:08,090
Nobody is in the wrong.

423
00:31:08,810 --> 00:31:10,650
Don't you know your mom's temper?

424
00:31:11,030 --> 00:31:12,210
She's too stubborn.

425
00:31:12,630 --> 00:31:14,850
But she met a person who is
more stubborn than her.

426
00:31:15,150 --> 00:31:16,790
No one is willing to back down.

427
00:31:16,790 --> 00:31:17,960
So they got divorced.

428
00:31:18,260 --> 00:31:20,060
But I think they had

429
00:31:20,060 --> 00:31:21,700
a close relationship.

430
00:31:21,700 --> 00:31:23,000
It was a pity.

431
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,480
Chen Jun He actually

432
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,740
cares about you two.

433
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,300
All these years, your mom and I

434
00:31:29,300 --> 00:31:30,600
invested in stocks

435
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,110
and funds.

436
00:31:32,110 --> 00:31:33,080
Actually,

437
00:31:33,790 --> 00:31:34,760
that money

438
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,520
all came from Chen Jun He.

439
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:38,200
A few days ago,

440
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:40,770
he asked me about you and your mother.

441
00:31:41,140 --> 00:31:42,780
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

442
00:31:42,780 --> 00:31:44,630
How could I tell you earlier?

443
00:31:44,630 --> 00:31:46,350
I can only tell you now

444
00:31:46,350 --> 00:31:47,910
because you're all grown up and sensible.

445
00:31:48,870 --> 00:31:51,090
From now on, persuade your mother

446
00:31:51,090 --> 00:31:52,060
to change her temper.

447
00:31:52,060 --> 00:31:54,250
Just back down a little when she needs to.

448
00:31:54,630 --> 00:31:55,680
Did you hear me?

449
00:31:57,270 --> 00:31:57,940
Well now.

450
00:31:58,700 --> 00:31:59,200
I still have things to do.

451
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,000
I have to go.

452
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:00,660
Godmother.

453
00:32:02,090 --> 00:32:02,970
One more thing.

454
00:32:03,450 --> 00:32:06,050
Do you have a former classmate
named Duan Xiao?

455
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,910
Duan Xiao...

456
00:32:10,250 --> 00:32:10,750
Right.

457
00:32:10,750 --> 00:32:11,800
There was a Duan Xiao.

458
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:13,820
How did you know him?

459
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:16,170
Could you please tell me about him?

460
00:32:16,170 --> 00:32:18,360
Why do you want to know about him?

461
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:19,660
I have my reason.

462
00:32:19,660 --> 00:32:20,750
Just don't ask.

463
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:22,810
I only want to know

464
00:32:22,810 --> 00:32:24,280
what he looks like,

465
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,500
where he is

466
00:32:25,740 --> 00:32:26,800
and what he is doing now.

467
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:29,650
What are you thinking of all day?

468
00:32:31,420 --> 00:32:33,010
In our ex-classmates chat group...

469
00:32:33,010 --> 00:32:34,020
Yesterday

470
00:32:34,020 --> 00:32:36,790
or the day before,
someone posted some old photos.

471
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:38,510
I'll find it for you.

472
00:32:40,950 --> 00:32:41,700
Here.

473
00:32:42,710 --> 00:32:43,510
Take a look.

474
00:32:51,410 --> 00:32:52,630
Which one is him?

475
00:32:53,130 --> 00:32:54,460
The one on the far left

476
00:32:54,460 --> 00:32:56,070
with the biggest smile.

477
00:33:00,230 --> 00:33:00,900
It's...

478
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,200
It's impossible.

479
00:33:02,200 --> 00:33:03,210
He was my classmate.

480
00:33:03,210 --> 00:33:04,680
How couldn't I recognise him?

481
00:33:07,490 --> 00:33:08,330
This guy

482
00:33:08,330 --> 00:33:09,590
was a love fool.

483
00:33:10,220 --> 00:33:11,360
During our school days,

484
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:14,890
he adored a girl in the next class.

485
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:17,450
What was her name?

486
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:20,180
I can't remember.

487
00:33:20,180 --> 00:33:21,020
Anyway,

488
00:33:21,020 --> 00:33:22,610
he was so fond of that girl.

489
00:33:22,610 --> 00:33:23,870
The way he treated her

490
00:33:23,870 --> 00:33:25,180
was exceptional.

491
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:28,900
But later the girl transferred
to another school.

492
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:31,350
He had an unrequited love for a long time.

493
00:33:31,350 --> 00:33:33,370
We all felt sorry for him.

494
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:35,380
Alright now.

495
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:36,850
I have to go.

496
00:33:37,610 --> 00:33:38,360
Godmother.

497
00:33:38,780 --> 00:33:39,750
Could you

498
00:33:39,750 --> 00:33:41,180
do me one more favor?

499
00:33:42,690 --> 00:33:45,040
It's about last month.

500
00:33:45,590 --> 00:33:46,390
Reservation under Miss Fan.

501
00:33:46,390 --> 00:33:47,560
Okay. This way please.

502
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:48,360
Thank you.

503
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:50,630
That's right. I haven't received
the commission for last month.

504
00:33:50,630 --> 00:33:51,510
Can you hurry up?

505
00:33:52,060 --> 00:33:53,940
If you don't, I'll take this to Mr He.
Do you hear me?

506
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:56,840
Alright.

507
00:34:09,060 --> 00:34:09,570
Miss,

508
00:34:09,780 --> 00:34:10,489
what do you like to order?

509
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:11,699
I'll order later.

510
00:34:11,699 --> 00:34:12,889
My friend is not here yet.

511
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:37,290
[Miss Wang]

512
00:34:38,460 --> 00:34:39,350
Your phone is ringing.

513
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:42,920
[Miss Wang]

514
00:34:44,260 --> 00:34:44,889
It's fine.

515
00:34:44,889 --> 00:34:45,650
It's...

516
00:34:45,650 --> 00:34:47,120
It's about work. It's not important.

517
00:34:49,469 --> 00:34:50,850
Are you going to order or not?

518
00:34:51,270 --> 00:34:52,239
Keep it down.

519
00:34:52,659 --> 00:34:54,380
Just serve us anything

520
00:34:54,380 --> 00:34:55,600
and don't talk to us anymore.

521
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,230
Thank you.

522
00:34:56,730 --> 00:34:57,320
Okay.

523
00:35:00,430 --> 00:35:02,100
I can't hear anything.

524
00:35:03,860 --> 00:35:05,430
Are you still working
at the plastic surgery hospital?

525
00:35:08,750 --> 00:35:10,300
Why don't give yourself a plastic surgery?

526
00:35:11,470 --> 00:35:12,440
It's too expensive. I have no money.

527
00:35:13,910 --> 00:35:15,720
How do you know where I work?

528
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:17,190
Why don't I know?

529
00:35:18,030 --> 00:35:19,240
I know everything about you.

530
00:35:21,510 --> 00:35:23,070
You heard it from Fan Shui Shui?

531
00:35:23,950 --> 00:35:25,380
She invited you here, right?

532
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:27,980
Your mom is smiling.

533
00:35:29,110 --> 00:35:30,290
Is she?

534
00:35:31,970 --> 00:35:33,400
Did Chen Jun He smile?

535
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:35,160
What are they talking about?

536
00:35:35,160 --> 00:35:37,220
I didn't know she invited you.

537
00:35:38,020 --> 00:35:39,180
What do you mean?

538
00:35:39,180 --> 00:35:40,500
If you knew, you wouldn't come?

539
00:35:41,130 --> 00:35:42,470
No.

540
00:35:42,470 --> 00:35:43,860
I'm afraid you won't come.

541
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:46,920
Why won't I come?

542
00:35:47,470 --> 00:35:49,020
I'm not afraid of you.

543
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:54,900
Now that we're here,

544
00:35:54,900 --> 00:35:55,990
let's eat something.

545
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:58,600
Or should we wait for Fan Shui Shui?

546
00:35:58,600 --> 00:35:59,560
She'll not come.

547
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,870
Can't you see it?

548
00:36:00,870 --> 00:36:02,040
Do you think she'll come?

549
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:03,550
Let's order some food then.

550
00:36:03,930 --> 00:36:04,770
Go ahead.

551
00:36:04,770 --> 00:36:05,570
It's on me.

552
00:36:05,570 --> 00:36:06,120
Alright then.

553
00:36:06,450 --> 00:36:07,800
I want cattle belly.

554
00:36:09,060 --> 00:36:10,820
Are you really doing this?

555
00:36:11,450 --> 00:36:12,640
Doing what?

556
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:14,100
You can get the bill if you want to.

557
00:36:14,100 --> 00:36:15,480
I don't want to treat you.

558
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:16,530
Why me?

559
00:36:16,530 --> 00:36:17,910
Why can't it be you?

560
00:36:17,910 --> 00:36:18,790
Chen Jun He,

561
00:36:18,790 --> 00:36:20,820
why haven't you changed
after all these years?

562
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:22,410
You own a big kindergarten

563
00:36:22,410 --> 00:36:23,290
but you're letting pay

564
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:24,470
for a hotpot?

565
00:36:24,470 --> 00:36:25,650
Aren't you embarrassed?

566
00:36:27,830 --> 00:36:29,380
So you have been asking around
about me too.

567
00:36:32,980 --> 00:36:34,800
Who cares enough to do that?

568
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:35,560
I...

569
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:37,780
I heard Fan Shui Shui talk about it.

570
00:36:38,790 --> 00:36:39,380
Anyway, I don't care.

571
00:36:39,380 --> 00:36:40,550
It's on you today.

572
00:36:40,970 --> 00:36:41,730
Excuse me.

573
00:36:41,730 --> 00:36:42,220
We're ready to order.

574
00:36:42,990 --> 00:36:44,080
Alright. Coming.

575
00:36:46,430 --> 00:36:47,320
Get down.

576
00:36:47,780 --> 00:36:49,120
Don't let them see you.

577
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:50,420
Keep this a covert operation.

578
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:53,200
Godmother,

579
00:36:53,530 --> 00:36:55,300
why did they get divorced?

580
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:57,610
Listen.

581
00:36:58,070 --> 00:36:58,990
Chen Jun He...

582
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:00,290
You haven't ordered the soup base.

583
00:37:06,130 --> 00:37:06,930
How about

584
00:37:07,770 --> 00:37:08,610
having a drink?

585
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:09,910
I quit drinking.

586
00:37:09,910 --> 00:37:10,790
I drink tea now.

587
00:37:11,680 --> 00:37:13,230
That sounds healthy.

588
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:15,160
Of course.

589
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,210
After being single for so many years,

590
00:37:17,210 --> 00:37:18,940
I should treat myself better.

591
00:37:19,610 --> 00:37:20,870
What do you mean?

592
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,220
You blame me?

593
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:24,280
Who should I blame then?

594
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:25,620
If it weren't for you, would I be single?

595
00:37:26,330 --> 00:37:28,600
You said you wanted a divorce.

596
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:30,530
When did I say that?

597
00:37:30,530 --> 00:37:32,090
If it weren't you,
how could we get divorced?

598
00:37:32,090 --> 00:37:34,150
Didn't you say you want a divorce?

599
00:37:34,150 --> 00:37:34,820
I...

600
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:36,670
When did I say that?

601
00:37:44,350 --> 00:37:44,940
Well.

602
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:47,670
I got divorced somehow

603
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:48,840
and became a single mom.

604
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,650
I got divorced somehow

605
00:37:50,990 --> 00:37:52,580
but I don't even have a child.

606
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:54,720
You blame me?

607
00:37:55,690 --> 00:37:58,670
You insisted on marrying me.

608
00:37:58,670 --> 00:38:00,340
Was it me to blame?

609
00:38:00,340 --> 00:38:01,860
Who knew you really wanted a divorce?

610
00:38:01,860 --> 00:38:03,380
I didn't said I wanted a divorce.

611
00:38:03,380 --> 00:38:05,390
When I wanted to talk to you
about this at the door,

612
00:38:05,390 --> 00:38:07,110
you said you didn't want to listen.

613
00:38:07,110 --> 00:38:08,960
Of course I didn't want to listen.

614
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,800
I didn't want to hear you giving thanks.

615
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:12,200
Why should I listen to that?

616
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:12,990
But,

617
00:38:12,990 --> 00:38:16,060
how would you know
what I was going to say?

618
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:16,400
You...

619
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:19,080
I actually wanted to ask if
we can continue to stay married.

620
00:38:19,080 --> 00:38:20,300
Of course we can.

621
00:38:35,300 --> 00:38:36,560
That's it?

622
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:37,560
What's wrong with it?

623
00:38:37,900 --> 00:38:38,950
You're a successful entrepreneur

624
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:40,210
but you're giving me a ride on a bike?

625
00:38:40,210 --> 00:38:41,430
This is BMW.

626
00:38:41,710 --> 00:38:43,280
A good bike is way expensive than a car.

627
00:38:44,690 --> 00:38:46,470
Pink helmet?

628
00:38:46,850 --> 00:38:48,270
Chen Jun He.

629
00:38:48,740 --> 00:38:50,790
Do you always take girls home?

630
00:38:50,790 --> 00:38:52,520
Do you know why you have been single

631
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:53,820
for so many years?

632
00:38:53,820 --> 00:38:55,160
It's because you are not faithful.

633
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:55,960
You're not...

634
00:39:11,580 --> 00:39:13,890
Can you not stand so close to me?

635
00:39:13,890 --> 00:39:14,900
Stay away from me.

636
00:39:15,190 --> 00:39:16,660
We're getting old.

637
00:39:21,580 --> 00:39:22,420
This is not right.

638
00:39:23,220 --> 00:39:24,430
Do you know where my house is?

639
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:25,570
I do.

640
00:39:26,240 --> 00:39:27,580
Have you been stalking me?

641
00:39:27,580 --> 00:39:28,340
Why would I stalk you?

642
00:39:28,340 --> 00:39:29,310
Am I crazy?

643
00:39:30,190 --> 00:39:31,030
Get on.

644
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:12,270
Yes.

645
00:40:13,740 --> 00:40:15,670
You really want them to be together?

646
00:40:16,220 --> 00:40:17,860
As long as Li Qing Tong is happy,

647
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:18,860
I can do anything.

648
00:40:20,250 --> 00:40:23,270
Our little girl has grown up.

649
00:40:24,810 --> 00:40:25,420
That's enough for today.

650
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:26,420
Let them

651
00:40:26,420 --> 00:40:28,220
take care of their own affairs.

652
00:40:28,220 --> 00:40:29,530
Our operation

653
00:40:29,530 --> 00:40:31,080
is a great success.

654
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:34,660
Godmother.

655
00:40:35,490 --> 00:40:36,670
Are you hungry?

656
00:40:38,390 --> 00:40:40,070
I kept staring at them just now

657
00:40:40,070 --> 00:40:41,120
and didn't touch the food at all.

658
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,680
I'm starving now.

659
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:43,430
Should we go eat?

660
00:40:43,430 --> 00:40:44,180
Let's go.

661
00:40:57,710 --> 00:40:58,640
Li Jin Bu.

662
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,420
You're not sick, right?

663
00:41:08,380 --> 00:41:09,890
Let me see. Are you okay?

664
00:41:10,470 --> 00:41:11,350
I'm fine.

665
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:15,480
In that case...

666
00:41:16,110 --> 00:41:18,250
Are you hiding something from me?

667
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:19,760
No.

668
00:41:22,540 --> 00:41:23,540
But the moment I came back,

669
00:41:23,540 --> 00:41:24,380
you were doing housework.

670
00:41:24,380 --> 00:41:25,180
I...

671
00:41:25,390 --> 00:41:27,310
My mind can't accept this.

672
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,790
You cooked these?

673
00:41:36,220 --> 00:41:38,160
When did you learn how to
cook northeastern cuisine?

674
00:41:38,860 --> 00:41:39,540
I...

675
00:41:40,010 --> 00:41:40,840
I learned it online.

676
00:41:41,850 --> 00:41:42,900
Mom, sit down.

677
00:41:43,950 --> 00:41:44,790
Sit down.

678
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:46,180
Wait a minute.

679
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:00,250
Taste it.

680
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:15,120
Mom.

681
00:42:16,920 --> 00:42:18,310
It's not tasty?

682
00:42:24,230 --> 00:42:25,110
It's good.

683
00:42:26,370 --> 00:42:27,300
It is.

684
00:42:29,810 --> 00:42:30,870
You have grown up.

685
00:42:33,430 --> 00:42:34,350
It's good.

686
00:42:35,190 --> 00:42:36,190
I'll eat more.

687
00:42:44,690 --> 00:42:45,860
You overslept again.

688
00:42:45,860 --> 00:42:48,090
Li Jin Bu, time to get up!

689
00:43:23,450 --> 00:43:23,940
Mom,

690
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,170
I'm going to school.

691
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:26,100
See you tonight.

692
00:43:37,940 --> 00:43:38,650
Fan Shui Shui.

693
00:43:39,410 --> 00:43:40,040
Well...

694
00:43:40,250 --> 00:43:42,350
Should I put eggs or tomatoes first

695
00:43:42,350 --> 00:43:43,610
for scrambled eggs with tomatoes?

696
00:43:45,540 --> 00:43:45,880
Okay.

697
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:46,680
I got it.

698
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:48,060
Alright. Bye.

699
00:43:50,500 --> 00:43:51,000
Mom.

700
00:43:52,390 --> 00:43:53,100
You're home.

701
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,570
Why are you home so early?

702
00:43:54,860 --> 00:43:56,500
I happen to be free today.

703
00:43:56,500 --> 00:43:58,050
So I came back to make you dinner.

704
00:43:58,050 --> 00:43:59,650
You have cooked for me so many times.

705
00:43:59,650 --> 00:44:01,040
I'll show you my cooking skill tonight.

706
00:44:01,590 --> 00:44:02,470
Well,

707
00:44:02,470 --> 00:44:03,640
go have some fruits first.

708
00:44:15,490 --> 00:44:16,830
Whose phone is this?

709
00:44:17,410 --> 00:44:18,090
It's for you.

710
00:44:18,090 --> 00:44:18,760
Take it.

711
00:44:19,390 --> 00:44:21,530
How can we afford this?

712
00:44:22,150 --> 00:44:23,630
Don't worry about that.

713
00:44:23,630 --> 00:44:25,060
Your mom have some money now.

714
00:44:26,240 --> 00:44:27,080
Thank you, mom.

715
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:29,630
Open it.

716
00:44:30,980 --> 00:44:31,490
I made soup too.

717
00:44:31,490 --> 00:44:32,370
I'll get it.

718
00:44:39,260 --> 00:44:40,220
Mom.

719
00:44:44,550 --> 00:44:45,770
It's too ugly.

720
00:44:45,770 --> 00:44:47,070
I'm going to post it in my social media.

721
00:44:47,070 --> 00:44:48,040
It's not okay. Take another one.

722
00:44:48,040 --> 00:44:48,920
Come on.

723
00:45:01,390 --> 00:45:02,060
What are you doing?

724
00:45:02,990 --> 00:45:04,420
Who are you texting?

725
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:05,930
It's none of your business.

726
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:08,830
Who is He He?

727
00:45:10,630 --> 00:45:12,310
You're so annoying.

728
00:45:12,310 --> 00:45:14,080
Why did you peek?

729
00:45:14,580 --> 00:45:15,250
Be serious.

730
00:45:15,250 --> 00:45:16,600
Are you wrong?

731
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:17,690
I'm wrong.

732
00:45:18,860 --> 00:45:19,450
Be serious.

733
00:45:19,450 --> 00:45:20,290
What's that?

734
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:21,670
Well.

735
00:45:22,550 --> 00:45:23,690
School holiday is coming.

736
00:45:24,150 --> 00:45:26,090
Let's go back to Tieyuan and have a look.

737
00:45:27,680 --> 00:45:28,980
Go back to Tieyuan now?

738
00:45:29,280 --> 00:45:31,340
It's very cold over there.
Can you bear it?

739
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:39,360
[Station Exit]

740
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:40,410
Your hands are cold, right?

741
00:45:40,620 --> 00:45:40,950
Here.

742
00:45:40,950 --> 00:45:41,840
Put it in my pocket.

743
00:45:46,370 --> 00:45:47,420
Are you cold?

744
00:45:48,180 --> 00:45:49,060
No.

745
00:45:49,060 --> 00:45:50,360
I'm used to it.

746
00:45:50,360 --> 00:45:51,870
I'm not afraid of the cold at all.

747
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:53,680
Used to it?

748
00:45:53,680 --> 00:45:55,440
How many times have you been here?

749
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:56,620
I don't understand why you have to

750
00:45:56,620 --> 00:45:57,960
come all the way back to Tieyuan?

751
00:45:57,960 --> 00:45:59,480
You really make me worry.

752
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:01,370
I just want to see

753
00:46:01,370 --> 00:46:03,800
the place you grew up in.

754
00:46:04,310 --> 00:46:05,310
Didn't I tell you?

755
00:46:05,650 --> 00:46:07,200
Back then in Tieyuan,

756
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:08,670
I was all-powerful

757
00:46:08,670 --> 00:46:10,270
and known as the "first lady of Tieyuan".

758
00:46:10,820 --> 00:46:12,030
You won't believe me anyway.

759
00:46:12,030 --> 00:46:12,830
Fine.

760
00:46:13,250 --> 00:46:14,380
Tell me everything again.

761
00:46:14,760 --> 00:46:15,730
I'll believe you.

762
00:46:16,990 --> 00:46:17,620
Let's go home.

763
00:46:19,050 --> 00:46:20,180
The other way.

764
00:46:20,980 --> 00:46:21,820
The other way?

765
00:46:21,820 --> 00:46:22,450
Yes.

766
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:23,750
I'm the "first lady of Tieyuan".

767
00:46:23,750 --> 00:46:25,640
How can I not know the way?

768
00:46:29,250 --> 00:46:31,400
What are you doing, Li Jin Bu?

769
00:46:32,150 --> 00:46:33,190
You don't want your suitcase?

770
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:21,670
Feng Xia...

771
00:47:25,990 --> 00:47:27,590
You're always fooing around.

772
00:47:30,870 --> 00:47:31,660
Why don't you try wearing it too?

773
00:47:31,660 --> 00:47:32,550
Go away.

774
00:48:42,980 --> 00:48:44,350
You don't remember everything here, right?

775
00:48:45,410 --> 00:48:46,840
You were only six

776
00:48:47,210 --> 00:48:48,060
when you came here.

777
00:48:54,190 --> 00:48:55,160
Li Qing Tong.

778
00:48:57,170 --> 00:48:59,230
Did you have a lot of friends
when you were a kid?

779
00:48:59,640 --> 00:49:01,670
Not a lot.

780
00:49:01,670 --> 00:49:02,830
Just overwhelmingly a lot.

781
00:49:02,830 --> 00:49:04,230
Fine.

782
00:49:06,750 --> 00:49:07,340
Li Qing Tong.

783
00:49:07,340 --> 00:49:07,930
What?

784
00:49:09,610 --> 00:49:11,160
There's something I want to
discuss with you.

785
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:11,830
Go ahead.

786
00:49:13,430 --> 00:49:14,770
I don't want to be your daughter anymore.

787
00:49:17,240 --> 00:49:17,960
What?

788
00:49:18,670 --> 00:49:19,670
Do you want to rebel again?

789
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:25,060
Let's be friends.

790
00:49:31,950 --> 00:49:33,750
I don't want to be friends with you.

791
00:49:59,260 --> 00:50:03,840
[The End]

792
00:50:08,660 --> 00:50:10,880
Everyone, please put down your pens.

793
00:50:10,880 --> 00:50:13,780
Let me introduce a new classmate to you.

794
00:50:15,880 --> 00:50:16,640
Hi, everyone.

795
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:17,600
I'm Zhou Yan Chen.

796
00:50:17,600 --> 00:50:18,640
Nice to meet you.
